OL,3,C2024 set to be hottest year on record,
OL,4,Ccapping a 'decade of deadly heat'
OL,6,F"This is climate breakdown, in real
OL,7,Ftime. We must exit this road to ruin
OL,8,Fand we have no time to lose.
OL,10,F"In 2025, countries must put the world
OL,11,Fon a safer path by dramatically
OL,12,Fslashing emissions and supporting the
OL,13,Ftransition to a renewable future. It
OL,14,Fis essential, and it is possible."
OL,16,FWMO secretary-general Celeste Saulo
OL,17,Fsaid every degree of warming matters
OL,18,Fand leads to increased climate
OL,19,Fextremes, with temperatures "only part
OL,20,Fof the picture".
