OL,3,C2024 set to be hottest year on record,
OL,4,Ccapping a 'decade of deadly heat'
OL,6,FThe WMO pointed to a new report that
OL,7,Ffound climate change intensified 26 of
OL,8,Fthe 29 extreme weather events studied
OL,9,Fby World Weather Attribution (WWA) in
OL,10,F2024, which killed at least 3,700
OL,11,Fpeople and displaced millions.
OL,13,FClimate change added 41 days of
OL,14,Fdangerous heat in 2024, according to
OL,15,Fthe report from WWA, a network of
OL,16,Fscientists who examine the role of
OL,17,Fglobal warming in extreme weather
OL,18,Fevents, and research and reporting
OL,19,Forganisation Climate Central.
